Metropolitan Life Insurance Co. NY Cuts Position in Ecolab Inc. (NYSE:ECL)


					Posted by Lucas Kauffman on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments




Metropolitan Life Insurance Co. NY decreased its position in shares of  Ecolab Inc. (NYSE:ECL) by 1.3% during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The fund owned 140,338 shares of the basic materials company’s stock after selling 1,901 shares during the period. Metropolitan Life Insurance Co. NY’s holdings in Ecolab were worth $17,590,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. FUKOKU MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE Co increased its position in  Ecolab by 60.0% in the first quarter. FUKOKU MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE Co now owns 800 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $100,000 after buying an additional 300 shares during the last quarter.  JNBA Financial Advisors increased its position in  Ecolab by 2.5% in the first quarter. JNBA Financial Advisors now owns 871 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $109,000 after buying an additional 21 shares during the last quarter.  Harfst & Associates Inc. bought a new position in  Ecolab during the first quarter worth about $117,000.  Guardian Life Insurance Co. of America increased its position in  Ecolab by 0.7% in the first quarter. Guardian Life Insurance Co. of America now owns 1,012 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $127,000 after buying an additional 7 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, State of Alaska Department of Revenue bought a new position in  Ecolab during the first quarter worth about $134,000. Institutional investors own  75.79% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Ecolab Inc. alerts:



Ecolab Inc. (NYSE ECL) opened at 132.45 on Thursday. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $132.94 and its 200-day moving average is $126.39. The company has a market cap of $38.42 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 31.29 and a beta of 0.98. Ecolab Inc. has a 12 month low of $110.65 and a 12 month high of $134.89. 





Ecolab (NYSE:ECL) last released its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The basic materials company reported $0.80 EPS for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.81 by $0.01. Ecolab had a net margin of 9.47% and a return on equity of 18.96%. The business had revenue of $3.17 billion during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $3.16 billion. During the same quarter last year, the business posted $0.77 earnings per share. The company’s quarterly revenue was up 2.2% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, analysts anticipate that  Ecolab Inc. will post $4.78 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Monday, July 17th. Shareholders of record on Tuesday, June 20th were paid a $0.37 dividend. This represents a $1.48 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.12%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Friday, June 16th. Ecolab’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 34.91%. 
